[2] Response
- Wed 21 Nov 2018. DRC: MSF base robbed in South Kivu "hideout territory"
[Actualite, in French, machine trans., edited]
https://actualite.cd/2018/11/21/rdc-une-base-de-msf-cambriolee-au-sud-kivu
[Byline: Justin Mwamba]

"On the evening of Tue 20 Nov 2018, the base of the humanitarian organization Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF), located in Lulimba, in the territory of Fizi, was the subject of an armed robbery committed by unidentified men, valuable goods were taken away, but no one was seriously injured," an MSF/Holland official in South Kivu said.

In this hideout territory of armed groups, MSF is supporting the Baraka and Lulimba hospitals in the care of cholera patients.

A convoy of this NGO, which left the city of Uvira for the city of Baraka with drugs, was looted [Fri 16 Nov 2018] by armed men at the village Muchimuchi, located 7 kilometers [4.4 mi] from Baraka, in the territory of Fizi (South Kivu), according to concordant sources.

Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) temporarily left its Tushunguti base in the Bunyakiri health zone, Kalehe territory (South Kivu), following violent clashes between 2 Mai-Mai factions (Raia Mutomboki). All the medical staff had been relocated and temporarily installed at the Numbi base, about 3 by motorcycle from Tushunguti. The NGO returned to this locality after a return to calm.

--
