[3] Vaccine: RFI
Date: Wed 21 Nov 2018
From: Karl Johnson <microcaddis@gmail.com> [edited]


Can anyone report details of the vaccination campaign? We need to know how many, if any, of those vaccinated came down with Ebola disease, and also the interval before onset, as well as the outcome of infection.

Remember, the original work with non-human primates told of lifesaving results post-vaccination after virus inoculation. These data are vital to get the "unproven" label from a product that is clearly most important in disease prevention.

--
Karl M Johnson MD
<microcaddis@gmail.com>

[ProMED thanks Dr Johnson [who led the team that originally discovered and named Ebola virus in Zaire - Mod.JH] for this question and welcomes any information readers have to offer. It is important to know details of the response to the vaccine and not merely that it is effective. - Mod.LK]
